Interesting:
&quot;Hailed as a wonder find by John McGraw when the Giants signed him out of TCU in 1909, Drucke was 12-10 in 1910. He struck out 151 in 215 innings but was wild. His career was cut short when he ruptured an arm muscle in a subway accident.&quot;
His last game in the majors was May 1, 1912. He died in Waco, TX, in 1955.
